The <i>actual</i> reason that third function compiles, and the fourth does not, is that<p><pre><code>    {
      x: 0
    }
</code></pre>
is a <i>block statement</i> with a <i>label</i> x. Try it in your console, it returns 0. The last one is an object literal outside an expression, which is a syntax error.<p>In addition to that, the return statement is &#x27;restricted production&#x27; where the line break itself is a terminator, this has nothing to do with semi-colons or ASI.
